description.narrative: UNICEF successfully supported Somalis with the application for the second dose of measles and IPV (polio) vaccinations and the introduction of the COVAX vaccine. The second measles and IPV doses will be introduced into the routine immunisation schedule in 2021 offering further protection to Somali children, while the COVAX vaccine application is currently being reviewed by GAVI for potential introduction in June 2021. 94% of the Effective Vaccine Management Plan (2017-2020) was implemented and as a result 2 million children under 5 have been reached with an integrated package of measles & polio vaccinations, Vitamin A, and deworming. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:03/01/2021
